    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I could imagine that https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/pull/3507 which hasn't yet made it into a release may help.  Without that change we weren't actually waiting for the database to shutdown cleanly, but we still shouldn't lose blocks even if there's a non-clean shutdown.\n\nThe transaction to record finalized blocks is committed prior to even starting the transaction to prune them from the hot database so not sure how this would happen other than RocksDB losing the finalized transaction entirely but managing to keep the later hot db prune transaction.",
