    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The only thing I can see that could happen here is that the archive database lost a transaction which had been committed and the hot database managed to keep its transaction even though it occurred entirely after the first commit.  That's pretty unexpected but not impossible.\n\nIt does strongly suggest that with the move we're likely to do to leveldb we should use the combined database so archive and hot data is in a single database and this problem is avoided.  Unfortunately RocksDB's memory usage explodes when we try to use a combined db with it so a fix will be dependent on moving to leveldb.\n\nGoing to close this out as I don't believe there's anything more we can do on it and leveldb migration has its own stream of tickets.",
